                    <msContents>

                        <summary>
                            <seg type="para"> This fragment is a single folio; it was probably
                                originally an endleaf. It contains a <title> Possession note of a
                                    lexicon from Mount Sinai</title>, containing a threat against
                                whoever would want to take the manuscript. </seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Erika Elia</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc"> Greek</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
                            <!--<locus from="[1]r" to="[1]v">ff. [1]r-[1]v</locus>-->
                            <title type="desc" xml:lang="en"> Possession note of a monastery on
                                Mount Sinai</title>
                            <incipit>
                        <locus from="[1]v" to="[1]v">f. [1]v</locus> Τοῦτο τὸ λεξικὸν
                                ἔναι τοῦ ἁγίου ὄρους Σινᾶ· καὶ εἴ τις τὸ θέλει πάρειν αἵναι
                                ἀφορισμένος</incipit>
                            <note> The transcription portrays the original orthography</note>
                            <note> Under the note there are two words written in monocondyle,
                                probably a name, difficult to decipher, which maybe could be read
                                as: <unclear> Εὐγένιος</unclear>
                                <unclear>ἐπίσκοπος</unclear> (?)</note>
                        </msItem>

                    </msContents>

