                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <locus from="[1]v" to="[1]v">f. [1]v</locus> Hand A: the possession
                                note was written in black ink by a hand that can be possibly placed
                                in the 15th or 16th century. The script is upright, the letters are
                                divided, uprights tends to be extended below the line; the forms can
                                be reconducted to the galaxy of scripts deriving from the <term>
                                    minuscule τῶν Ὁδηγῶν</term>, widespread in the Eastern regions
                                after the fall of Byzantium. </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <additions> The leaf is marked on <locus from="[1]r" to="[1]r"> f.
                                [1]r</locus> with the current classmark and the former classmark
                            T.23 (i.e. Tischendorf 23). </additions>
                    </physDesc>

